doc_summary_long: The office of the Canadian prime minister Justin Trudeau has forced Fox News to apologise and retract a 'false and misleading' tweet that inaccurately described the suspect in the Québec City mosque shooting as a man of Moroccan origin. 'Islamophobia killed Canadians': anti-Muslim rhetoric blamed in Québec attack. Kate Purchase, the director of communications for the prime minister's office, sent a letter to Fox News objecting to misinformation it had put out after the attack on the Québec City Islamic cultural center.
doc_summary_short: The office of the Canadian prime minister Justin Trudeau has forced Fox News to apologise and retract a 'false and misleading' tweet that inaccurately described the suspect in the Québec City mosque shooting as a man of Moroccan origin.
doc_title: Fox News deletes false Québec shooting tweet after Canadian PM's office steps in
